| New Year w/ my faves.✨🫶🏽

| The second hardest year of my life by far. From recovering from a miscarriage, to losing my grandmother, and leaving a life that I thought I wanted. God obviously had other plans, plans that I don’t question or doubt.

I can honestly say, I’m where I’m supposed to be right now. And starting over doesn’t mean that you’ve failed, it only means you were brave enough to try again.

I pray that I never have to experience a year like this ever again. That hopefully in this new year I truly find my purpose, become my own boss, knock out my goals, and if by chance find love (because I still haven’t given up on that). All of the things I deserve are coming to me. I claim it. A new me is here, and I’m excited to see her flourish. 

Thank you to my mom, sisters, brother, friends, and those who chose to still love me through/despite my darkest times. I would not have survived without your love and support, and holding me up when I didn’t have the strength to do so myself. I’ll never forget what some of you have done for me this year.

I’m so blessed to have this platform, and I promise to keep growing. To keep sharing my faith, spreading love, and helping those who are also fighting.

This video reminds me that 2022 wasn’t all bad. 

But 2023, be good to me please! 🫶🏽

| I’m learning on this journey that if I sit in my grief, I’ll never allow myself the chance to move forward. To live. Today was hard. It was one of those random days where grief decided to greet me at the door as soon as I opened my eyes. I allowed myself the opportunity to cry, to release whatever I was feeling but then deciding that I can not allow myself to rot.

I decided to be intentional and to love on myself today. To do small things that make me happy, and in return it brought me back to a place of joy that the grief tried to steal this morning. I’ve been very open about my grief journey. As you all know, I’ve experienced it more than I’d like to. So in a way this has become my journal, and I’d like to share it with you all. Because if I can help one person, save someone, help someone else not feel like they’re on this grief journey alone… then I know I will have made my Dad proud. So here we go..

The small things series. 🤍

#grief #griefjourney #life #growingthroughgrief #journaling #griefawareness #griefsupport

| Thirteen years ago my sister @yourstruly_ang came to me and told me that she would be giving her daughter my middle name, Monét. And of course I was filled with excitement, but being so young I didn’t truly understand the magnitude of how special that was until later in life. Over the years I would brag about having children around the world named after myself, Niy was always the first one that I spoke of. I don’t have children of my own, so it was kind of like my sister Angie was sharing a piece of her with me.. and that’s something that I will forever hold dear to my heart. 

So when @joyybyrd reached out to me about helping make her ‘Butterfly Garden’ vision come to life for Aniyah, I was honored. We spent night and day working on the butterfly and decor, we knew it had to be perfect. I hope you all felt it was too. 

I filmed the process not only for myself and Joy, but also for you, Angie. I hope you know how much Aniyah is loved and cherished. Since I got the news, a day has not gone by where I don’t think of her. She is so special to me. Thank you for sharing her with me and the rest of this world. We were so blessed to experience such a strong, resilient, and beautiful soul. I told you the world will know of her as long as I’m alive, this is just the beginning for our little Butterfly. Love you and Niy, forever.🦋🫶🏽💗

| Sometimes God will allow certain things to happen in your life, that lead you back to him because he’s all you’ve got. This is something I’ve been meaning to do since January 2023, and I allowed so many distractions to get in the way that I finally told myself ‘you have to make time for Him too’. If I’m honest, I’ve been running from God. But that stops here. And if you’ve ever wondered why my faith is so strong despite all that I’ve been through, it’s because I’m a living example of what he can do. So many blessings have happened for me behind closed doors and even though they may be too personal to share, I can boldly say that God’s hand has never left mine. He’s walked me through every storm, all the pain, the times when I didn’t know how something was going to work out… he was always there making a way. My relationship with God has been a journey, but it’s one that I’m not ashamed of. This prayer board is only the beginning… 

God, show me how good it can get. 🙏🏽🤍

#prayer #prayerboard #faith #prayerworks #newbeginnings

| Two years ago, I was about to become a mom. But on this day I had that title stripped away from me. My life has felt like a journey of never-ending pain, and I’m so badly trying to find the light in the midst of so much darkness. I feel like my purpose in this life is to be a mother. To live in a body with so much love, and no one to give it to has been quite lonely. But I know amongst it all, God is just preparing me. He’s preparing me to be a better wife, mother, friend, for when the time comes. This was never a life that I intended for myself, but I’ve figured out that it’s not about me. That maybe my story, my journey, my woes… are simply a testimony meant for someone else.
